- Provide sustained capacity development support to the relevant legislative committees, including by offering tailored training;
- Help establish additional divisions of Court E in Gbarnga (Bong) and Sanniquellie (Nimba) and salaries for public defenders;
- Provide sustained capacity development support to the Public Safety Division in the Ministry of Justice with a view to ensuring proper oversight of private security companies;
- Support the establishment of the Civilian Complaints Review Board;
- Underpin critical law reforms aimed at reducing case backlogs and assist with the establishment of a proper plea-bargaining system;
- Strengthen the capacity of selected CSOs/CBOs to provide legal aid and assistance;
- Raise public awareness of available legal aid services;
- Strengthen clinical legal education, including by helping to set up a legal aid clinic at the Louis Arthur Grimes Law School; 
- Provide sustained capacity development support to the Kofi Annan Institute for Conflict Transformation, with a view to providing a platform for SSR education and dialogue;
- Commission a study on how Liberians use informal justice mechanisms and what kind of outcomes they achieve;
- Support the sensitization of prosecutorial, judicial and legal staff on the rights and needs of women and girls, with a view to reducing discriminatory attitudes and behaviours and strengthening gender responsiveness across the justice ‘chain’; 
- Provide tailored legal aid services to women and girls;
- Commission an independent outcome evaluation to assess the level of progress made towards achieving the outputs and outcomes articulated in the programme document; and 
- Undertake regular M&E assessments of all activities and interventions
-

	Developed/produced practical guidelines on parliamentary oversight and human rights-based legal reforms;
	Developed/produced video documentary on experience sharing and mentoring containing interviews and counsels from former law makers;
	Supported the establishment of two divisions of Court E in Bong and Nimba Counties and provided salary and logistical supports for their operations
	Supported the establishment of a Civilian Complaint Review Board for the Liberia National Police and the Liberia Immigration Services; the Board is functional and has begun receiving and hearing complaints from the two entities;
	Supported the amendment of five sections of the Criminal Procedure Law on Plea-bargaining, Arrest, Terms of Court, Relieving Judge and Standard of Preliminary Examination; the amended sections have been validated and being finalized for submission to the National Legislature;
	Provided technical and financial support to nine (9) CSOs to provide legal aid services to indigents including SGBV survivors, pre-trial detainees, children in conflict with the law, etc. CSO supported include Center for Justice and Peace Studies (CJPS), Citizens’ Initiative for Dialogue (CID), Rural Integrated Center for Community Empowerment (RICCE), Survivors Aid International Liberia (SAIL), Development Education Network Liberia (DEN-L), Prison Fellowship Liberia (PFL), Foundation for International Dignity (FIND), Her Voice Liberia (HVL) and Institute for Democratic Action and Development (IDAD)
	 Developed a framework to guide the processes for the establishment of a legal aid clinic at the Louis Arthur Grimes School of Law of the University of Liberia;
	Conducted two refresher trainings for justice chain actors including lawyers, police, social workers, judges, prosecutors, etc.;
	Commissioned and conducted an independent outcome evaluation of the Joint Rule of Law Programme Phase II; the evaluation was completed, and report submitted with findings and recommendations to the Programme Board; and
	 Supported the conduct of policy dialogues with citizens on security sector reforms and a research on patterns and underlying factors to community violence through a partnership with the Kofi Annan Institute of Conflict Transformation of the University of Liberia.
